description.narrative:
1) Number of national policies and plans (identified) that incorporate PES and biocarbon financing mechanism in support of CBFCM; 
2) Existence of a multi-agency / multi-sectoral mechanism for CBFCM/ PES – biocarbon dialogue, consultation with inclusive participation from all relevant government organizations, CSOs, academia, private sector and CBFCM community networks; 
3) Institutional capacities strengthened at national (M&E Office) and regional levels (4 pilot REO training centres) to implement PES and biocarbon financing schemes in support of CBFCM ;
4) Number and Type of PES and biocarbon financing schemes developed and applied (in place) for CBFCM in the 4 pilot sites.

comment.narrative:
1) Forestry and catchment management policies and legal instruments currently have limited inclusion of CBFCM; 
2) No central oversight body exist for PES/ biocarbon implementation;
3) Existing training and capacity building programmes for REOs do not include PES/biocarbon methods; 
4) Currently there are no PES and biocarbon financing strategies and schemes developed and/or applied for CBFCM within the 4 REO pilot site regions.

1) The REO Strategic Plan  (2017-2021)  incorporating PES as an economic instrument to support natural resources and environmental management implemented with 4 REO integrating PES in their action plans; 
2) No Ad Working Group established at the national level due to an inadequate institutional buy-in; 
3) PES and Biocarbon curriculum developed and integrated into REO official trainings; 
4) 1 PES agreement developed and started implementation in Mae Sa Pilot Site; for the rest of the 3 pilot sites - there were MOUs with potential private sector and state-enterprises partners developed.

